The paper focuses on the quality assessment of Big Data, which involves processing, analyzing, and extracting knowledge from large datasets. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper's emphasis on data quality and its review of existing methods also suggests a focus on practical applications and real-world challenges, which aligns with the themes of these sub-categories.
